{"key":"processedPost-6492186","value":{"id":6492186,"first":6492005,"last":6492316,"when":1169660273,"utime":"01/24/07 07:37 PM","content":"Take your pick.  I usually advise against doing anything to an already fruiting substrate under the reasoning of not fixing what isn't broken. However, others have added a casing layer at your point and been successful.<br /><br />One thing to consider though is all those trichoderma spores from the other trays.  If they got on your substrate, they probably won't do much harm, but if you put a casing layer over them, it could stimulate them to germinate and grow.<br />RR","title":"Re: apply casing layer to fruiting substrate?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}